.Bo.Hu.1","L.Delle.Rose.1","M.Sahin.2","T.Dorigo.1","J.Maillard.1","C.MuletMarquis.6","Dou.Wang.1","A.Coccaro.1","A.Jaiswal.2","Nima.Arkani.Hamed.1","Kelci.Mohrman.1","F.Cataneo.1","P.Levchenko.1","P.Kubinec.20","M.Guchait.1","Jing.Ya.Zhu.1","E.Cogneras.1","C.Fu.4","Albrecht.Wagner.1","M.Moreno.Llacer.1","E.Sideras.Haddad.1","V.I.M.Outschoorn.1","H.Vink.1","Zhi.Deng.1","F.Badaud.1","P.Z.Ngcobo.1"],"figures":[{"filename":"EEC-examples.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Example distributions of the EEC as a function of $\\theta_{\\rm L}$ (top) and $z$ (bottom) using a ``flipped double-log style\" as described in the main text. The various regions of the distribution are marked for illustration purposes, where the green represents the free hadron (or soft emission) region, the blue represents the quark/gluon region, and the gray represents the transition between these two regions. The collinear region (where $\\theta_{\\rm L}\\sim 0$ and $z \\sim 0$) and the back-to-back or Sudakov region (where $\\theta_{\\rm L}\\sim\\pi$ and $z \\sim 1$) is also marked.","label":"fig:ENCcollinearsudakov","source":"arxiv","key":"06feb8b960f8e0bbd9ee3ce5facc40fb","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/06feb8b960f8e0bbd9ee3ce5facc40fb"},{"filename":"EEC-examples_z.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Example distributions of the EEC as a function of $\\theta_{\\rm L}$ (top) and $z$ (bottom) using a ``flipped double-log style\" as described in the main text. The various regions of the distribution are marked for illustration purposes, where the green represents the free hadron (or soft emission) region, the blue represents the quark/gluon region, and the gray represents the transition between these two regions. The collinear region (where $\\theta_{\\rm L}\\sim 0$ and $z \\sim 0$) and the back-to-back or Sudakov region (where $\\theta_{\\rm L}\\sim\\pi$ and $z \\sim 1$) is also marked.","label":"fig:ENCcollinearsudakov","source":"arxiv","key":"df834c44b7111bce35c917148cd004eb","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/df834c44b7111bce35c917148cd004eb"},{"filename":"Thrust-examples.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Example distribution of thrust (left) and $\\log \\tau$ (right). The thrust distribution clearly separates two distinct QCD regimes: the perturbative multi-jet region at lower thrust values (light blue), characterized by a broad distribution from isotropic particle production, and the non-perturbative dijet region (light green) at high thrust values near unity. The sharp dijet peak located just below the thrust maximum results from Sudakov form factor suppression, which represents the probability of no additional parton emission. This suppression makes perfect two-jet configurations less probable, creating the characteristic peaked structure. The $\\log \\tau$ parameterization provides an enhanced view of the non-perturbative region by expanding the logarithmic scale, offering detailed resolution of the peak structure that complements the linear thrust binning.","label":"fig:thrustLogTau","source":"arxiv","key":"d8b77e79e087bddd595acb1694ac209d","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/d8b77e79e087bddd595acb1694ac209d"},{"filename":"delphi.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Schematic of the DELPHI detector.","label":"fig:delphi","source":"arxiv","key":"acb63f87fc2698da1d210881d8ac9225","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/acb63f87fc2698da1d210881d8ac9225"},{"filename":"comp_TrackPTSele_1994.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Comparisons of track $p_{\\rm T}$, $\\theta$, and $\\phi$ in 1994 data (black), reconstructed PYTHIA~5.7/JETSET~7.4 (red), ARIADNE (green), PYTHIA 8.3 (orange), and PYTHIA 8.3 Dire (brown) samples. Note that the corresponding number of selected events of each sample normalizes the distributions.","label":"fig:MCdatacomp1","source":"arxiv","key":"46365e06881cee1dd19cf7da0646da77","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/46365e06881cee1dd19cf7da0646da77"},{"filename":"comp_TrackThetaSele_1994.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Comparisons of track $p_{\\rm T}$, $\\theta$, and $\\phi$ in 1994 data (black), reconstructed PYTHIA~5.7/JETSET~7.4 (red), ARIADNE (green), PYTHIA 8.3 (orange), and PYTHIA 8.3 Dire (brown) samples. Note that the corresponding number of selected events of each sample normalizes the distributions.","label":"fig:MCdatacomp1","source":"arxiv","key":"9a5ac79847bb6c1f7521b522a6b11bc4","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/9a5ac79847bb6c1f7521b522a6b11bc4"},{"filename":"comp_TrackPhiSele_1994.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Comparisons of track $p_{\\rm T}$, $\\theta$, and $\\phi$ in 1994 data (black), reconstructed PYTHIA~5.7/JETSET~7.4 (red), ARIADNE (green), PYTHIA 8.3 (orange), and PYTHIA 8.3 Dire (brown) samples. Note that the corresponding number of selected events of each sample normalizes the distributions.","label":"fig:MCdatacomp1","source":"arxiv","key":"65cbf5bad462c4196174de79784a927b","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/65cbf5bad462c4196174de79784a927b"},{"filename":"comp_TrackPTSele_1995.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Comparisons of track $p_{\\rm T}$, $\\theta$, and $\\phi$ in 1995 data (black), reconstructed PYTHIA~5.7/JETSET~7.4 (red), ARIADNE (green), PYTHIA 8.3 (orange), and PYTHIA 8.3 Dire (brown) samples. Note that the corresponding number of selected events of each sample normalizes the distributions.","label":"fig:MCdatacomp195","source":"arxiv","key":"0116a12407e594dbc9738157df098a66","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/0116a12407e594dbc9738157df098a66"},{"filename":"comp_TrackThetaSele_1995.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Comparisons of track $p_{\\rm T}$, $\\theta$, and $\\phi$ in 1995 data (black), reconstructed PYTHIA~5.7/JETSET~7.4 (red), ARIADNE (green), PYTHIA 8.3 (orange), and PYTHIA 8.3 Dire (brown) samples. Note that the corresponding number of selected events of each sample normalizes the distributions.","label":"fig:MCdatacomp195","source":"arxiv","key":"0b2455493836a3f676d0de788e3bbf52","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/0b2455493836a3f676d0de788e3bbf52"},{"filename":"comp_TrackPhiSele_1995.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Comparisons of track $p_{\\rm T}$, $\\theta$, and $\\phi$ in 1995 data (black), reconstructed PYTHIA~5.7/JETSET~7.4 (red), ARIADNE (green), PYTHIA 8.3 (orange), and PYTHIA 8.3 Dire (brown) samples. Note that the corresponding number of selected events of each sample normalizes the distributions.","label":"fig:MCdatacomp195","source":"arxiv","key":"d2571817284bc574ca9434d439740dfe","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/d2571817284bc574ca9434d439740dfe"},{"filename":"comp_NuetralESele_1994.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Comparisons of neutral particle $E$, $\\theta$, and $\\phi$ in 1994 data (black), reconstructed PYTHIA~5.7/JETSET~7.4 (red), ARIADNE (green), PYTHIA 8.3 (orange), and PYTHIA 8.3 Dire (brown) samples. Note that the corresponding number of selected events of each sample normalizes the distributions.","label":"fig:MCdatacomp2","source":"arxiv","key":"ed548c57a511a79fc4a808d0abbe21f2","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/ed548c57a511a79fc4a808d0abbe21f2"},{"filename":"comp_NuetralThetaSele_1994.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Comparisons of neutral particle $E$, $\\theta$, and $\\phi$ in 1994 data (black), reconstructed PYTHIA~5.7/JETSET~7.4 (red), ARIADNE (green), PYTHIA 8.3 (orange), and PYTHIA 8.3 Dire (brown) samples. Note that the corresponding number of selected events of each sample normalizes the distributions.","label":"fig:MCdatacomp2","source":"arxiv","key":"ffca7b74cb1140e4a3253c3708eb54b8","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/ffca7b74cb1140e4a3253c3708eb54b8"},{"filename":"comp_NuetralPhiSele_1994.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Comparisons of neutral particle $E$, $\\theta$, and $\\phi$ in 1994 data (black), reconstructed PYTHIA~5.7/JETSET~7.4 (red), ARIADNE (green), PYTHIA 8.3 (orange), and PYTHIA 8.3 Dire (brown) samples. Note that the corresponding number of selected events of each sample normalizes the distributions.","label":"fig:MCdatacomp2","source":"arxiv","key":"fbb0cbe0ac23871a8d4201af6e560c94","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/fbb0cbe0ac23871a8d4201af6e560c94"},{"filename":"comp_NuetralESele_1995.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Comparisons of neutral particle $E$, $\\theta$, and $\\phi$ in 1995 data (black), reconstructed PYTHIA~5.7/JETSET~7.4 (red), ARIADNE (green), PYTHIA 8.3 (orange), and PYTHIA 8.3 Dire (brown) samples. Note that the corresponding number of selected events of each sample normalizes the distributions.","label":"fig:MCdatacomp295","source":"arxiv","key":"08e738c59fe2cb842df72cf76380baab","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/08e738c59fe2cb842df72cf76380baab"},{"filename":"comp_NuetralThetaSele_1995.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Comparisons of neutral particle $E$, $\\theta$, and $\\phi$ in 1995 data (black), reconstructed PYTHIA~5.7/JETSET~7.4 (red), ARIADNE (green), PYTHIA 8.3 (orange), and PYTHIA 8.3 Dire (brown) samples. Note that the corresponding number of selected events of each sample normalizes the distributions.","label":"fig:MCdatacomp295","source":"arxiv","key":"92539c5623823e0a2ec3154747f11ff0","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/92539c5623823e0a2ec3154747f11ff0"},{"filename":"comp_NuetralPhiSele_1995.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Comparisons of neutral particle $E$, $\\theta$, and $\\phi$ in 1995 data (black), reconstructed PYTHIA~5.7/JETSET~7.4 (red), ARIADNE (green), PYTHIA 8.3 (orange), and PYTHIA 8.3 Dire (brown) samples. Note that the corresponding number of selected events of each sample normalizes the distributions.","label":"fig:MCdatacomp295","source":"arxiv","key":"32797e4d8ff4bcdfc673c277a5fe7687","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/32797e4d8ff4bcdfc673c277a5fe7687"},{"filename":"comp_NChargedSele_1994.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Comparisons of the (a) 1994 charged track multiplicity, (b) 1994 all particle multiplicity, (c) 1995 charged track multiplicity, and (b) 1995 all particle multiplicity data (black), reconstructed PYTHIA~5.7/JETSET~7.4 (red), ARIADNE (green), PYTHIA 8.3 (orange), and PYTHIA 8.3 Dire (brown) samples. Note that the corresponding number of selected events of each sample normalizes the distributions.","label":"fig:MCdatacomp3","source":"arxiv","key":"e6cc8487139ca8d780814ba32b085b56","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/e6cc8487139ca8d780814ba32b085b56"},{"filename":"comp_NPartSele_1994.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Comparisons of the (a) 1994 charged track multiplicity, (b) 1994 all particle multiplicity, (c) 1995 charged track multiplicity, and (b) 1995 all particle multiplicity data (black), reconstructed PYTHIA~5.7/JETSET~7.4 (red), ARIADNE (green), PYTHIA 8.3 (orange), and PYTHIA 8.3 Dire (brown) samples. Note that the corresponding number of selected events of each sample normalizes the distributions.","label":"fig:MCdatacomp3","source":"arxiv","key":"7fa2302d7a762e43603ebe4acfcd097d","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/7fa2302d7a762e43603ebe4acfcd097d"},{"filename":"comp_NChargedSele_1995.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Comparisons of the (a) 1994 charged track multiplicity, (b) 1994 all particle multiplicity, (c) 1995 charged track multiplicity, and (b) 1995 all particle multiplicity data (black), reconstructed PYTHIA~5.7/JETSET~7.4 (red), ARIADNE (green), PYTHIA 8.3 (orange), and PYTHIA 8.3 Dire (brown) samples. Note that the corresponding number of selected events of each sample normalizes the distributions.","label":"fig:MCdatacomp3","source":"arxiv","key":"a067687ba8037e6a6bc499255af6bc56","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/a067687ba8037e6a6bc499255af6bc56"},{"filename":"comp_NPartSele_1995.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Comparisons of the (a) 1994 charged track multiplicity, (b) 1994 all particle multiplicity, (c) 1995 charged track multiplicity, and (b) 1995 all particle multiplicity data (black), reconstructed PYTHIA~5.7/JETSET~7.4 (red), ARIADNE (green), PYTHIA 8.3 (orange), and PYTHIA 8.3 Dire (brown) samples. Note that the corresponding number of selected events of each sample normalizes the distributions.","label":"fig:MCdatacomp3","source":"arxiv","key":"59e016cf27809218a174f3d69437a0d2","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/59e016cf27809218a174f3d69437a0d2"},{"filename":"comp_ThrustMissPNCDelphi_1994.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Comparisons of the thrust variables $\\tau$ (left) and $\\log\\tau$ (right) in 1994 data (black), reconstructed PYTHIA~5.7/JETSET~7.4 (red), ARIADNE (green), PYTHIA 8.3 (orange), and PYTHIA 8.3 Dire (brown) samples.","label":"fig:MCdatacomp4","source":"arxiv","key":"2ef20fe85e2e7bb9f3ac02e07569545e","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/2ef20fe85e2e7bb9f3ac02e07569545e"},{"filename":"comp_ThrustMissPNCLog2_1994.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Comparisons of the thrust variables $\\tau$ (left) and $\\log\\tau$ (right) in 1994 data (black), reconstructed PYTHIA~5.7/JETSET~7.4 (red), ARIADNE (green), PYTHIA 8.3 (orange), and PYTHIA 8.3 Dire (brown) samples.","label":"fig:MCdatacomp4","source":"arxiv","key":"ec926abf437d5a286dfe9da201935f4f","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/ec926abf437d5a286dfe9da201935f4f"},{"filename":"comp_ThrustMissPNCDelphi_1995.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Comparisons of the thrust variables $\\tau$ (left) and $\\log\\tau$ (right) in 1995 data (black), reconstructed PYTHIA~5.7/JETSET~7.4 (red), ARIADNE (green), PYTHIA 8.3 (orange), and PYTHIA 8.3 Dire (brown) samples.","label":"fig:MCdatacomp495","source":"arxiv","key":"1f9bb34e43f815c8deb00295f5d441d6","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/1f9bb34e43f815c8deb00295f5d441d6"},{"filename":"comp_ThrustMissPNCLog2_1995.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Comparisons of the thrust variables $\\tau$ (left) and $\\log\\tau$ (right) in 1995 data (black), reconstructed PYTHIA~5.7/JETSET~7.4 (red), ARIADNE (green), PYTHIA 8.3 (orange), and PYTHIA 8.3 Dire (brown) samples.","label":"fig:MCdatacomp495","source":"arxiv","key":"2f7cbe00888bbf2e390574424d710f43","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/2f7cbe00888bbf2e390574424d710f43"},{"filename":"comp_EEC_r_1994.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Comparisons of the EEC in data (black), reconstructed PYTHIA~5.7/JETSET~7.4 (red), ARIADNE (green), PYTHIA 8.3 (orange), and PYTHIA 8.3 Dire (brown) samples for 1994 (left) and 1995 (right).","label":"fig:MCdatacomp5","source":"arxiv","key":"ae2824afb2d4e5013b9ed16f382db648","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/ae2824afb2d4e5013b9ed16f382db648"},{"filename":"comp_EEC_r_1995.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Comparisons of the EEC in data (black), reconstructed PYTHIA~5.7/JETSET~7.4 (red), ARIADNE (green), PYTHIA 8.3 (orange), and PYTHIA 8.3 Dire (brown) samples for 1994 (left) and 1995 (right).","label":"fig:MCdatacomp5","source":"arxiv","key":"2bd264d6e17694a22d68d7871ec505af","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/2bd264d6e17694a22d68d7871ec505af"},{"filename":"Analysis-Flow.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Overview of the various steps of the analysis in their sequential order.","label":"fig:analysisOutline","source":"arxiv","key":"67bf095569e2c2c10f5741d4f4926096","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/67bf095569e2c2c10f5741d4f4926096"},{"filename":"MatchedPairCartoon.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Cartoon visualization of single track and pairwise matching. Tracks shown in blue are considered to be at the reconstructed (reco) level, and tracks shown in orange are considered to be at the generator (gen) level.","label":"fig:matchedPairCartoon","source":"arxiv","key":"b1d3de76c5a401d2c3d75b88a2be591e","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/b1d3de76c5a401d2c3d75b88a2be591e"},{"filename":"trk_eff_1995.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Single track matching efficiency from PYTHIA 5 MC as a function of generator-level $p_{\\rm T}$ (left) and $\\theta$ (right) for 1994 (black) and 1995 (red) samples, respectively. The upper panels show the distributions of matched (triangle markers) and all (circular and square markers) generator-level tracks, while the lower panels show the efficiency ratio.","label":"fig:trk_eff","source":"arxiv","key":"9081d0cef07999f48355f1dd18a25fbe","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/9081d0cef07999f48355f1dd18a25fbe"},{"filename":"trk_eff_theta_1995.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Single track matching efficiency from PYTHIA 5 MC as a function of generator-level $p_{\\rm T}$ (left) and $\\theta$ (right) for 1994 (black) and 1995 (red) samples, respectively. The upper panels show the distributions of matched (triangle markers) and all (circular and square markers) generator-level tracks, while the lower panels show the efficiency ratio.","label":"fig:trk_eff","source":"arxiv","key":"7d9dc5f536e92eb6040164538171e7d8","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/7d9dc5f536e92eb6040164538171e7d8"},{"filename":"trk_fake_1995.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Single track fake rate from PYTHIA 5 MC as a function of reconstructed $p_{\\rm T}$ (left) and $\\theta$ (right) for 1994 (black) and 1995 (red) samples, respectively. The upper panels show the distributions of matched (triangle markers) and all (circular and square markers) detector-level tracks, while the lower panels show the fake rate ratio.","label":"fig:trk_fake","source":"arxiv","key":"3c01c4cf3c68dd86688d790c5e8ffcc4","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/3c01c4cf3c68dd86688d790c5e8ffcc4"},{"filename":"trk_fake_theta_1995.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Single track fake rate from PYTHIA 5 MC as a function of reconstructed $p_{\\rm T}$ (left) and $\\theta$ (right) for 1994 (black) and 1995 (red) samples, respectively. The upper panels show the distributions of matched (triangle markers) and all (circular and square markers) detector-level tracks, while the lower panels show the fake rate ratio.","label":"fig:trk_fake","source":"arxiv","key":"3492b8f92228dfa9bd196054b682972c","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/3492b8f92228dfa9bd196054b682972c"},{"filename":"trk_res_theta.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Track $\\theta$ resolution distributions from PYTHIA 5 MC in different detector regions: forward endcap (left), barrel (middle), and backward endcap (right). The $\\theta$ response is calculated as $(\\theta_{\\rm reco} - \\theta_{\\rm gen}) / \\theta_{\\rm gen}$. Double Gaussian fits are overlaid to extract the resolution parameters. The figures here are for the 1994 sample only; the track angular resolution from the 1995 sample, shown in Appendix~\\ref{app:1995}, has a similar level of performance.","label":"fig:theta_res","source":"arxiv","key":"4ddf60b559b839cbe21e30816ed297a6","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/4ddf60b559b839cbe21e30816ed297a6"},{"filename":"trk_res_phi.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Track $\\phi$ resolution distributions from PYTHIA 5 MC in different detector regions: forward endcap (left), barrel (middle), and backward endcap (right). The $\\phi$ response is calculated as $(\\phi_{\\rm reco} - \\phi_{\\rm gen}) / \\phi_{\\rm gen}$. Double Gaussian fits are overlaid to extract the resolution parameters. The figures here are for the 1994 sample only; the track angular resolution from the 1995 sample, shown in Appendix~\\ref{app:1995}, has a similar level of performance.","label":"fig:phi_res","source":"arxiv","key":"f4d1211963a4fa79d2d194303f4d7d0e","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/f4d1211963a4fa79d2d194303f4d7d0e"},{"filename":"trk_res_pt_all.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Track $p_{\\rm T}$ resolution distributions from PYTHIA 5 MC in different $p_{\\rm T}$ ranges. The $p_{\\rm T}$ response is calculated as $p_{\\rm T, reco} / p_{\\rm T, gen}$. Double-sided crystal ball fits are overlaid to extract the response and resolution parameters. The figures here are for the 1994 sample only; the track momentum resolution from the 1995 sample, shown in Appendix~\\ref{app:1995}, has a similar level of performance.","label":"fig:phi_pt","source":"arxiv","key":"2f63f25802602e140cfde7d07d46cb37","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/2f63f25802602e140cfde7d07d46cb37"},{"filename":"response_matrix.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Unnormalized response matrix for EEC unfolding showing the correspondence between reconstructed (x-axis) and generator-level (y-axis) distributions for the $\\theta_{\\rm L}$ parametrization in 1994. Here, the 2D response matrix is visualized by structuring it so that each $\\theta_{\\rm L}$ bin forms a block containing all energy dimension correspondences. The strong correlation along the diagonal indicates good detector resolution.","label":"fig:response","source":"arxiv","key":"70ba0a4a8b247c6d1afc4b8b300e6967","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/70ba0a4a8b247c6d1afc4b8b300e6967"},{"filename":"EEC_unf_size.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Comparison of the unfolded (red) and raw (black) 1994 data distributions. The unfolded distribution shown here includes fake subtraction and efficiency correction.","label":"fig:unfoldEEC","source":"arxiv","key":"2c1c7460f2039af7b8740500cbbc2a41","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/2c1c7460f2039af7b8740500cbbc2a41"},{"filename":"EEC_fake_size.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Comparison of the response matrix  unfolded (red) and fake-subtracted (black) 1994 data distributions.","label":"fig:fakeCorrUnf","source":"arxiv","key":"3e00325feee724593e9b7b0ee86f9416","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/3e00325feee724593e9b7b0ee86f9416"},{"filename":"EEC_unf_only_size.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Comparison of the efficiency corrected (red) and response matrix unfolded (black) 1994 data distributions.","label":"fig:unfoldCorrUnf","source":"arxiv","key":"50ccc2460676f95d8fd9d5a3d37d9249","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/50ccc2460676f95d8fd9d5a3d37d9249"},{"filename":"EEC_unf_eff_size.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Comparison of the unfolded (red) and raw (black) 1994 data distributions.","label":"fig:effCorrUnf","source":"arxiv","key":"a6e92f8348cf994cce6430ddf50c3d20","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/a6e92f8348cf994cce6430ddf50c3d20"},{"filename":"covariance_full_1994.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Covariance matrix for 1994 data. Here, the 2D covariance matrix is visualized by structuring it so that each $\\theta_{\\rm L}$ bin forms a block containing all energy dimension correspondences.","label":"fig:covariance","source":"arxiv","key":"dd4251174eefaa7fa7eae00e23bc9d9e","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/dd4251174eefaa7fa7eae00e23bc9d9e"},{"filename":"covariance_1994.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Covariance (left) and correlation (right) matrices of the one-dimensional EEC distribution as a function of $\\theta_{\\rm L}$ from 1994 data.","label":"fig:correlation","source":"arxiv","key":"130a4c7825256b7908375a0a3c9b0371","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/130a4c7825256b7908375a0a3c9b0371"},{"filename":"correlation_1994.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Covariance (left) and correlation (right) matrices of the one-dimensional EEC distribution as a function of $\\theta_{\\rm L}$ from 1994 data.","label":"fig:correlation","source":"arxiv","key":"48e152e6db650ed7c78fdb8f94da9312","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/48e152e6db650ed7c78fdb8f94da9312"},{"filename":"stats_error_1994.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Statistical error from simple Poissonian statistics (orange) and full covariance matrix (blue) from 1994 data.","label":"fig:stat","source":"arxiv","key":"012aa8804ef4d76d6817134d6e1f0bc9","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/012aa8804ef4d76d6817134d6e1f0bc9"},{"filename":"covariance_unfolded_1994.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Covariance (left) and correlation (right) matrices of the one-dimensional EEC distribution as a function of $\\theta_{\\rm L}$ after unfolding for 1994.","label":"fig:covUnfold","source":"arxiv","key":"2de8c684cdba2ed5cc44700cdff14bf5","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/2de8c684cdba2ed5cc44700cdff14bf5"},{"filename":"correlation_unfolded_1994.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Covariance (left) and correlation (right) matrices of the one-dimensional EEC distribution as a function of $\\theta_{\\rm L}$ after unfolding for 1994.","label":"fig:covUnfold","source":"arxiv","key":"c8d1d662e5054a74e99be9d6f3fa3f59","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/c8d1d662e5054a74e99be9d6f3fa3f59"},{"filename":"EEC_binning_corr_size.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Comparison of the unfolded 1994 data before (black) and after (red) binning projection correction.","label":"fig:binningcorr","source":"arxiv","key":"fa66924d2ca3c1520ee1e95d6aef0248","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/fa66924d2ca3c1520ee1e95d6aef0248"},{"filename":"EEC_sele_corr_size.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Event selection efficiency corrections as a function of $\\theta_{\\rm L}$ for 1994. The ratio is shown in the bottom panel, which represents the inverse of the event selection efficiency correction.","label":"fig:evtSelCorr","source":"arxiv","key":"6a7b37e23529d4619d870512fcf804e6","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/6a7b37e23529d4619d870512fcf804e6"},{"filename":"EEC_trk_eff_uncert.png","material":"preprint","caption":"The relative uncertainty on the reconstructed track EEC distribution from the track efficiency variation. The effect is shown as the ratio of the varied result (with 2\\% of tracks removed) to the nominal result.","label":"fig:trackEffUncert","source":"arxiv","key":"9018db6d28cf403f080e7d7bdda64d95","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/9018db6d28cf403f080e7d7bdda64d95"},{"filename":"EEC_trk_scale_uncert.png","material":"preprint","caption":"The relative uncertainty on the reconstructed EEC distribution from the track momentum scale variation.","label":"fig:trackScaleUncert","source":"arxiv","key":"f45496024759b4dd955f9513471f18a2","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/f45496024759b4dd955f9513471f18a2"},{"filename":"EEC_trk_fake_uncert.png","material":"preprint","caption":"The relative uncertainty on the unfolded EEC distribution from the high-$p_T$ track contamination study.","label":"fig:trackFakeUncert","source":"arxiv","key":"bd1799018114960fb6f6faa566123dad","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/bd1799018114960fb6f6faa566123dad"},{"filename":"EEC_unf_match.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Nominal unfolded result (black) compared to results from an alternative matching scheme (red) and an alternative cut-off (teal).","label":"fig:matchinguncert","source":"arxiv","key":"2a33a30bdb597a7fe38b970cd162b068","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/2a33a30bdb597a7fe38b970cd162b068"},{"filename":"EEC_unf_model.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Comparison of the unfolded EEC distributions obtained using response matrices derived from four different generators: PYTHIA 5.7 (black), ARIADNE (teal), PYTHIA 8 (red), and PYTHIA 8 Dire (orange).","label":"fig:prior","source":"arxiv","key":"c6c10a0c0dae4806333acae1799cb87b","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/c6c10a0c0dae4806333acae1799cb87b"},{"filename":"EEC_unf_iter.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Comparison of the unfolded EEC distributions obtained using 3 (red), 4 (black, nominal), and 5 (teal) iterations in the D'Agostini method.","label":"fig:iter","source":"arxiv","key":"e5bb9108c6557740e595645db575fbc1","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/e5bb9108c6557740e595645db575fbc1"},{"filename":"EEC_binning_corr.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Unfolded data distributions corrected by binning projection correction factors derived from PYTHIA 5.7 (black), ARIADNE (teal), and PYTHIA 8 (red), and PYTHIA 8 Dire (orange).","label":"fig:binningCorrSys","source":"arxiv","key":"c76ecf11693438aa46b3be5c796811fb","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/c76ecf11693438aa46b3be5c796811fb"},{"filename":"EEC_sele_corr.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Unfolded data distributions corrected by track and event selection correction factors derived from PYTHIA 5.7 (black), ARIADNE (teal), PYTHIA 8 (red), and PYTHIA 8 Dire (orange).","label":"fig:acceptcorr","source":"arxiv","key":"7dc6d2c63da77123a6c5337591bea5ab","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/7dc6d2c63da77123a6c5337591bea5ab"},{"filename":"EEC_systs.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Summary of the systematic uncertainties. The total uncertainty (gray dashed) is calculated as the quadratic sum of the individual uncertainty sources, including event and track selection corrections~\\ref{sec:selectionUncert} (orange), unfolding model dependence~\\ref{sec:unfoldingUncert} (red), matching scheme~\\ref{sec:matchingUncert} (blue), 2D binning projection~\\ref{sec:projectionUncert} (teal), unfolding regularization strength~\\ref{sec:unfoldingUncert} (brown), track efficiency (olive) and momentum scale (pink)~\\ref{sec:trkUncert}, and fake~\\ref{sec:trackTail} (gold).","label":"fig:systematicSummary","source":"arxiv","key":"71ec29ce798624aef49c4caf258784cd","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/71ec29ce798624aef49c4caf258784cd"},{"filename":"response_matrix_thrustDelphi.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Response matrices for $\\tau$ (left) and $\\log\\tau$ (right).","label":"fig:responseThrust","source":"arxiv","key":"63cf2ec4a606c78f8a9f1ab0f8d4a66e","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/63cf2ec4a606c78f8a9f1ab0f8d4a66e"},{"filename":"response_matrix_thrust.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Response matrices for $\\tau$ (left) and $\\log\\tau$ (right).","label":"fig:responseThrust","source":"arxiv","key":"e46db76cde7a1be45d6a9bd14b3ee232","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/e46db76cde7a1be45d6a9bd14b3ee232"},{"filename":"Thrust_Delphi_unf_size.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Raw (black) and unfolded (red) data distributions for $\\tau$ (left) and $\\log\\tau$ (right). Also shown are the generator-level distributions from PYTHIA 5 (teal).","label":"fig:unfoldThrust","source":"arxiv","key":"9933ce5800e2b02e55f1d85493163c7d","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/9933ce5800e2b02e55f1d85493163c7d"},{"filename":"Thrust_log_unf_size.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Raw (black) and unfolded (red) data distributions for $\\tau$ (left) and $\\log\\tau$ (right). Also shown are the generator-level distributions from PYTHIA 5 (teal).","label":"fig:unfoldThrust","source":"arxiv","key":"4277bf802ec80f3d65b8cfc24926c17f","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/4277bf802ec80f3d65b8cfc24926c17f"},{"filename":"Thrust_Delphi_sele_corr_qqpy.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Unfolded data distributions before (red) and after (black) correction to the full phase space for $\\tau$ (left) and $\\log\\tau$ (right).","label":"fig:correctedThrust","source":"arxiv","key":"60c1838b50889b6a38471413177b7039","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/60c1838b50889b6a38471413177b7039"},{"filename":"Thrust_log_sele_corr_qqpy.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Unfolded data distributions before (red) and after (black) correction to the full phase space for $\\tau$ (left) and $\\log\\tau$ (right).","label":"fig:correctedThrust","source":"arxiv","key":"632505256118a6b039dcd4ba710ace4b","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/632505256118a6b039dcd4ba710ace4b"},{"filename":"Thrust_Delphi_cEff_var.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Effect of the charged particle efficiency uncertainty on the reconstructed $\\tau$ (left) and $\\log\\tau$ (right) distributions. The nominal MC is shown in red, the varied MC (with 2\\% of tracks removed) is in teal, and the data is shown in black for reference.","label":"fig:effChargedSysThrust","source":"arxiv","key":"c4ceedb0febedcfad90b3e7b30577797","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/c4ceedb0febedcfad90b3e7b30577797"},{"filename":"Thrust_log_cEff_var.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Effect of the charged particle efficiency uncertainty on the reconstructed $\\tau$ (left) and $\\log\\tau$ (right) distributions. The nominal MC is shown in red, the varied MC (with 2\\% of tracks removed) is in teal, and the data is shown in black for reference.","label":"fig:effChargedSysThrust","source":"arxiv","key":"51095ef5b53293f2747152acf1f3ec75","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/51095ef5b53293f2747152acf1f3ec75"},{"filename":"Thrust_Delphi_cScale_var.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Effect of the charged particle momentum scale uncertainty on the reconstructed $\\tau$ (left) and $\\log\\tau$ (right) distributions. The nominal MC (red) is compared to the varied MC (teal) where track momenta have been shifted, and the data is shown in black for reference.","label":"fig:scaleChargedSysThrust","source":"arxiv","key":"00f73fa0ace19d146767cc2b5128ccb7","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/00f73fa0ace19d146767cc2b5128ccb7"},{"filename":"Thrust_log_cScale_var.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Effect of the charged particle momentum scale uncertainty on the reconstructed $\\tau$ (left) and $\\log\\tau$ (right) distributions. The nominal MC (red) is compared to the varied MC (teal) where track momenta have been shifted, and the data is shown in black for reference.","label":"fig:scaleChargedSysThrust","source":"arxiv","key":"3360026ede3b33a11b3656bd5dc9e330","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/3360026ede3b33a11b3656bd5dc9e330"},{"filename":"Thrust_Delphi_fake_var.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Estimation of the uncertainty from potential high-$p_{\\rm T}$ fake track contamination. The nominal data distribution (black) is compared to the varied data distribution (red), where a fraction of tracks with $p_{\\rm T} > 30$ GeV has been randomly removed.","label":"fig:tailChargedSysThrust","source":"arxiv","key":"e7ca1499a5c9f8293c1e3a70ac8965ac","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/e7ca1499a5c9f8293c1e3a70ac8965ac"},{"filename":"Thrust_log_fake_var.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Estimation of the uncertainty from potential high-$p_{\\rm T}$ fake track contamination. The nominal data distribution (black) is compared to the varied data distribution (red), where a fraction of tracks with $p_{\\rm T} > 30$ GeV has been randomly removed.","label":"fig:tailChargedSysThrust","source":"arxiv","key":"9efe433be80a3ca03475a98149835999","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/9efe433be80a3ca03475a98149835999"},{"filename":"Thrust_Delphi_nEff_var.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Effect of the neutral particle efficiency uncertainty on the reconstructed $\\tau$ (left) and $\\log\\tau$ (right) distributions. The nominal MC (red) is compared to the varied MC (teal) with 2\\% of neutral particles removed. Data is shown in black for reference.","label":"fig:effNeutralSysThrust","source":"arxiv","key":"d98be9cfe29f315087af48dc7e89708f","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/d98be9cfe29f315087af48dc7e89708f"},{"filename":"Thrust_log_nEff_var.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Effect of the neutral particle efficiency uncertainty on the reconstructed $\\tau$ (left) and $\\log\\tau$ (right) distributions. The nominal MC (red) is compared to the varied MC (teal) with 2\\% of neutral particles removed. Data is shown in black for reference.","label":"fig:effNeutralSysThrust","source":"arxiv","key":"0f21d61c154e78a5fb967f106c7f52ef","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/0f21d61c154e78a5fb967f106c7f52ef"},{"filename":"Thrust_Delphi_nScale_var.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Effect of the neutral particle energy scale uncertainty on the reconstructed $\\tau$ (left) and $\\log\\tau$ (right) distributions. The nominal MC (red) is compared to the varied MC (teal), where neutral particle energies have been shifted by 20\\%. Data is shown in black for reference.","label":"fig:scaleNeutralSysThrust","source":"arxiv","key":"b0f19db2508d1ebe45a85d2acedcec80","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/b0f19db2508d1ebe45a85d2acedcec80"},{"filename":"Thrust_log_nScale_var.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Effect of the neutral particle energy scale uncertainty on the reconstructed $\\tau$ (left) and $\\log\\tau$ (right) distributions. The nominal MC (red) is compared to the varied MC (teal), where neutral particle energies have been shifted by 20\\%. Data is shown in black for reference.","label":"fig:scaleNeutralSysThrust","source":"arxiv","key":"a98463b2aa9a81ae924e5e09a07b8c4f","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/a98463b2aa9a81ae924e5e09a07b8c4f"},{"filename":"Thrust_Delphi_sele_corr_comp_varEmin.png","material":"preprint","caption":"The relative uncertainty on the unfolded thrust distributions from varying the minimum neutral particle energy cut. The effect is shown as the ratio of the varied result (\\(E_{\\text{neutral}} > 5.0\\)~GeV) (red) to the nominal result (\\(E_{\\text{neutral}} > 0.5\\)~GeV) (black).","label":"fig:cutNeutral","source":"arxiv","key":"aab921263b237975d84fa66da806fd65","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/aab921263b237975d84fa66da806fd65"},{"filename":"Thrust_log_sele_corr_comp_varEmin.png","material":"preprint","caption":"The relative uncertainty on the unfolded thrust distributions from varying the minimum neutral particle energy cut. The effect is shown as the ratio of the varied result (\\(E_{\\text{neutral}} > 5.0\\)~GeV) (red) to the nominal result (\\(E_{\\text{neutral}} > 0.5\\)~GeV) (black).","label":"fig:cutNeutral","source":"arxiv","key":"a83a0341f94c1d38ef5801e4c404c1e9","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/a83a0341f94c1d38ef5801e4c404c1e9"},{"filename":"Thrust_Delphi_multiWeight.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Effect of the event multiplicity reweighting on the reconstructed \\(\\tau\\) (left) and \\(\\log\\tau\\) (right) distributions. The nominal 1994 MC (red) is compared to the varied 1994 MC (teal), which has been reweighted to match the multiplicity distribution of the 1995 data. The 1994 data is shown in black for reference.","label":"fig:multiCorr","source":"arxiv","key":"a419d428f1e633b91a3e0669eb930506","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/a419d428f1e633b91a3e0669eb930506"},{"filename":"Thrust_log_multiWeight.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Effect of the event multiplicity reweighting on the reconstructed \\(\\tau\\) (left) and \\(\\log\\tau\\) (right) distributions. The nominal 1994 MC (red) is compared to the varied 1994 MC (teal), which has been reweighted to match the multiplicity distribution of the 1995 data. The 1994 data is shown in black for reference.","label":"fig:multiCorr","source":"arxiv","key":"fd6582040958f6ff6255cee9f3911072","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/fd6582040958f6ff6255cee9f3911072"},{"filename":"Thrust_Delphi_sim_model.png","material":"preprint","caption":"The relative uncertainty on the unfolded thrust distributions from using an alternative detector model. The effect is shown as the ratio of the result unfolded with the 1995 MC response matrix (red) to the nominal result unfolded with the 1994 MC matrix (black).","label":"fig:responseSys","source":"arxiv","key":"121f3b1754c7354b59d5a81411f3cc61","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/121f3b1754c7354b59d5a81411f3cc61"},{"filename":"Thrust_log_sim_model.png","material":"preprint","caption":"The relative uncertainty on the unfolded thrust distributions from using an alternative detector model. The effect is shown as the ratio of the result unfolded with the 1995 MC response matrix (red) to the nominal result unfolded with the 1994 MC matrix (black).","label":"fig:responseSys","source":"arxiv","key":"4d4bae9e5953002c6c7b732c94984954","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/4d4bae9e5953002c6c7b732c94984954"},{"filename":"Thrust_Delphi_unf_model.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Unfolded thrust (left) and $\\log\\tau$ (right) distributions using response matrices derived from PYTHIA 5 (black), PYTHIA 8 (red), ARIADNE (teal), and PYTHIA 8 Dire (orange).","label":"fig:unfoldThrustModel","source":"arxiv","key":"b70898638926a585c3d1be3e69d511f6","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/b70898638926a585c3d1be3e69d511f6"},{"filename":"Thrust_log_unf_model.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Unfolded thrust (left) and $\\log\\tau$ (right) distributions using response matrices derived from PYTHIA 5 (black), PYTHIA 8 (red), ARIADNE (teal), and PYTHIA 8 Dire (orange).","label":"fig:unfoldThrustModel","source":"arxiv","key":"0668ae7c4c9d8a6d2f1a34c50745a184","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/0668ae7c4c9d8a6d2f1a34c50745a184"},{"filename":"Thrust_Delphi_sele_corr.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Unfolded $\\tau$ (left) and $\\log\\tau$ (right) distributions corrected by acceptance correction factors derived from PYTHIA 5 (black), PYTHIA 8 (red), ARIADNE (teal), and PYTHIA 8 Dire (orange).","label":"fig:corrThrustModel","source":"arxiv","key":"9322a69d48829e8f393f58c3e10ee700","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/9322a69d48829e8f393f58c3e10ee700"},{"filename":"Thrust_log_sele_corr.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Unfolded $\\tau$ (left) and $\\log\\tau$ (right) distributions corrected by acceptance correction factors derived from PYTHIA 5 (black), PYTHIA 8 (red), ARIADNE (teal), and PYTHIA 8 Dire (orange).","label":"fig:corrThrustModel","source":"arxiv","key":"7570e1037064d04e1ebcbb6c3e27cd66","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/7570e1037064d04e1ebcbb6c3e27cd66"},{"filename":"Thrust_Delphi_systs.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Summary of systematic uncertainties for $\\tau$ (left) and $\\log\\tau$ (right) measurements.","label":"fig:sysSummaryThrust","source":"arxiv","key":"c693866309f28e50072bd069ee00bc62","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/c693866309f28e50072bd069ee00bc62"},{"filename":"Thrust_log_systs.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Summary of systematic uncertainties for $\\tau$ (left) and $\\log\\tau$ (right) measurements.","label":"fig:sysSummaryThrust","source":"arxiv","key":"7fbdc0dcc78792d6fbb235dd684dfed1","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/7fbdc0dcc78792d6fbb235dd684dfed1"},{"filename":"ee-logo.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Fully-corrected EEC distributions from the DELPHI open data as a function of $\\theta_{\\rm L}$. Statistical error bars are displayed as vertical lines, and systematic error bars are shown in the gray boxes. Predictions from PYTHIA 8 default, Vincia, and Dire parton shower algorithms are shown in blue, green, and red, respectively.Fully-corrected EEC distributions from the DELPHI open data as a function of $z$. Statistical error bars are displayed as vertical lines, and systematic error bars are shown in the gray boxes. Predictions from PYTHIA 8 default, Vincia, and Dire parton shower algorithms are shown in blue, green, and red, respectively.Fully-corrected thrust distributions for the 1994 and 1995 datasets. Statistical uncertainties are displayed as vertical error bars, and the total systematic uncertainties are shown as gray boxes. The data are compared to predictions from three PYTHIA~8 parton shower models: default (blue), Vincia (green), and Dire (red).Comparison of fully-corrected thrust (\\(\\tau\\)) distributions. The new all-particle measurement from this work for 1994 (gray) is shown with statistical uncertainties as vertical lines and total uncertainties as gray boxes. This is compared with the 1995 result from this work (teal), a legacy track-only measurement from 1994~\\cite{DELPHI:2000uri} (red), and a legacy all-particle measurement from 1991-1993~\\cite{DELPHI:1996sen} (orange). For these latter three datasets, the error bars represent the statistical and systematic uncertainties added in quadrature.","label":"fig:resultsEECr","source":"arxiv","key":"73085b346cfc1948c3c21b7dcab32a6e","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/73085b346cfc1948c3c21b7dcab32a6e"},{"filename":"EEC_DELPHI_EPJC_2000.png","material":"preprint","caption":"A comparison of the fully-corrected, track-based EEC distribution from this work (light coral) with the previous DELPHI measurement from Ref.~\\cite{DELPHI:2000uri} (gray). For the measurement from this work, the statistical uncertainties are shown as vertical lines, and the total systematic uncertainties are shown as boxes. For the previous measurement, the error bars represent the statistical and systematic uncertainties added in quadrature. The definition of the EEC in this work differs from that of the legacy DELPHI analysis. Specifically, the legacy measurement normalizes the energy of charged track pairs by the visible event energy, while the current work uses the beam energy.","label":"fig:delphi_epjc","source":"arxiv","key":"30e6824cbd003f9bf86ee9877e7afa6f","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/30e6824cbd003f9bf86ee9877e7afa6f"},{"filename":"EEC_full_closure.png","material":"preprint","caption":"EEC from fully corrected simulated PYTHIA 5 sample (black) and the generator-level PYTHIA 5 sample (red). The fully corrected sample is lying on top of the simulated one, showing perfect closure.","label":"fig:fullclosure","source":"arxiv","key":"d2523c0c40b1eef63432a229d40cb7c7","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/d2523c0c40b1eef63432a229d40cb7c7"},{"filename":"Thrust_Delphi_sele_corr_qqpy_closure.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Thrust from fully corrected simulated PYTHIA 5 sample (black) and the generator-level PYTHIA 5 sample (red). The fully corrected sample is lying on top of the simulated one, showing perfect closure.","label":"fig:fullclosure","source":"arxiv","key":"a4b9bf5a4991eb45741f1a7da30bda8e","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/a4b9bf5a4991eb45741f1a7da30bda8e"},{"filename":"trk_eff_pythia.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Single track matching efficiency as a function of PYTHIA 8 generator-level $p_{\\rm T}$ (left) and $\\theta$ (right). The upper panels show the distributions of matched (red) and all (black) generator-level tracks, while the lower panels show the efficiency ratio.","label":"fig:trk_eff_pythia","source":"arxiv","key":"7fa4367e90f693f4005d825f9df5e9f0","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/7fa4367e90f693f4005d825f9df5e9f0"},{"filename":"trk_eff_theta_pythia.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Single track matching efficiency as a function of PYTHIA 8 generator-level $p_{\\rm T}$ (left) and $\\theta$ (right). The upper panels show the distributions of matched (red) and all (black) generator-level tracks, while the lower panels show the efficiency ratio.","label":"fig:trk_eff_pythia","source":"arxiv","key":"d5bdc66fcc00467be78407fb70d2e959","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/d5bdc66fcc00467be78407fb70d2e959"},{"filename":"trk_fake_pythia.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Single track fake rate as a function of reconstructed PYTHIA 8 $p_{\\rm T}$ (left) and $\\theta$ (right). The upper panels show the distributions of matched (red) and all (black) reconstruction-level tracks, while the lower panels show the fake rate ratio.","label":"fig:trk_fake_pythia","source":"arxiv","key":"808168220e065cd7400513ff6b27a344","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/808168220e065cd7400513ff6b27a344"},{"filename":"trk_fake_theta_pythia.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Single track fake rate as a function of reconstructed PYTHIA 8 $p_{\\rm T}$ (left) and $\\theta$ (right). The upper panels show the distributions of matched (red) and all (black) reconstruction-level tracks, while the lower panels show the fake rate ratio.","label":"fig:trk_fake_pythia","source":"arxiv","key":"5ee31bdc63b6f876ecb3454d5089795f","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/5ee31bdc63b6f876ecb3454d5089795f"},{"filename":"EEC_comparison_Ks.png","material":"preprint","caption":"A generator-level comparison of the EEC distribution from a standard PYTHIA~8 sample (black) and a sample where $K^{0}_{\\rm S}$ decays have been disabled (red).","label":"fig:KsEEC","source":"arxiv","key":"39390e82f16c022dccb64ebe5ae6b353","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/39390e82f16c022dccb64ebe5ae6b353"},{"filename":"EEC_result_r_1994.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Fully-corrected EEC distributions from the 1994 DELPHI open data as a function of $\\theta_{\\rm L}$. Statistical error bars are displayed as vertical lines, and systematic error bars are shown in the gray boxes. Predictions from PYTHIA 8 default, Vincia, and Dire parton shower algorithms are shown in blue, green, and red, respectively.","label":"fig:resultsEECr94","source":"arxiv","key":"56dd21ebe4139847394121c28a32678d","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/56dd21ebe4139847394121c28a32678d"},{"filename":"EEC_result_z_1994.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Fully-corrected EEC distributions from the 1994 DELPHI open data as a function of $z$. Statistical error bars are displayed as vertical lines, and systematic error bars are shown in the gray boxes. Predictions from PYTHIA 8 default, Vincia, and Dire parton shower algorithms are shown in blue, green, and red, respectively.","label":"fig:resultsEECz94","source":"arxiv","key":"8fa627e5d85dc579ddd0ecef43abb713","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/8fa627e5d85dc579ddd0ecef43abb713"},{"filename":"EEC_result_r_1995.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Fully-corrected EEC distributions from the 1995 DELPHI open data as a function of $\\theta_{\\rm L}$. Statistical error bars are displayed as vertical lines, and systematic error bars are shown in the gray boxes. Predictions from PYTHIA 8 default, Vincia, and Dire parton shower algorithms are shown in blue, green, and red, respectively.","label":"fig:resultsEECr95","source":"arxiv","key":"5d370ce19befb6ca3ec4a9ab95e221e4","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/5d370ce19befb6ca3ec4a9ab95e221e4"},{"filename":"EEC_result_z_1995.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Fully-corrected EEC distributions from the 1995 DELPHI open data as a function of $z$. Statistical error bars are displayed as vertical lines, and systematic error bars are shown in the gray boxes. Predictions from PYTHIA 8 default, Vincia, and Dire parton shower algorithms are shown in blue, green, and red, respectively.","label":"fig:resultsEECz95","source":"arxiv","key":"c4e2b583c232716a7d4b53b885cbb1cc","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/c4e2b583c232716a7d4b53b885cbb1cc"},{"filename":"EEC_comp_ALEPH.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Comparison of the fully corrected EEC distributions from the 1994 (light coral) and 1995 (black) DELPHI datasets with the recent ALEPH re-analysis result~\\cite{Bossi:2025xsi} (blue). The ALEPH points include statistical uncertainties only.","label":"fig:compAleph","source":"arxiv","key":"ba524ffe153b9683233c9a1c08fb8b00","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/ba524ffe153b9683233c9a1c08fb8b00"},{"filename":"trk_res_theta_1995.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Track $\\theta$ resolution distributions for 1995 in different detector regions: forward endcap (left), barrel (middle), and backward endcap (right). The $\\theta$ response is calculated as $(\\theta_{\\rm reco} - \\theta_{\\rm gen}) / \\theta_{\\rm gen}$. Double Gaussian fits are overlaid to extract the resolution parameters.","label":"fig:theta_res_1995","source":"arxiv","key":"000a8d0b0eec7fc8f22a51f18a118d5f","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/000a8d0b0eec7fc8f22a51f18a118d5f"},{"filename":"trk_res_phi_1995.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Track $\\phi$ resolution distributions for 1995 in different detector regions: forward endcap (left), barrel (middle), and backward endcap (right). The $\\phi$ response is calculated as $(\\phi_{\\rm reco} - \\phi_{\\rm gen}) / \\phi_{\\rm gen}$. Double Gaussian fits are overlaid to extract the resolution parameters.","label":"fig:phi_res_1995","source":"arxiv","key":"e0c24eaf9fa3aac1fc991bde39ad2b72","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/e0c24eaf9fa3aac1fc991bde39ad2b72"},{"filename":"trk_res_pt_1995.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Track $p_{\\rm T}$ resolution distributions for 1995 in different $p_{\\rm T}$ ranges. The $p_{\\rm T}$ response is calculated as $p_{\\rm T, reco} / p_{\\rm T, gen}$. Double-sided crystal ball fits are overlaid to extract the response and resolution parameters.","label":"fig:phi_pt_1995","source":"arxiv","key":"92e988504d30709efd13840cccf54d74","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/92e988504d30709efd13840cccf54d74"},{"filename":"EEC_unf_model_1995.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Major systematic uncertainty: comparison of the unfolded EEC distributions obtained using response matrices derived from four different generators: PYTHIA 5 (black), PYTHIA 8 (red), and PYTHIA 8 Dire (teal).","label":"fig:phi_pt_1995","source":"arxiv","key":"02403aa049342a3c0248d3a2dd0cf5c9","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/02403aa049342a3c0248d3a2dd0cf5c9"},{"filename":"EEC_sele_corr_1995.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Major systematic uncertainty: unfolded data distributions corrected by track and event selection correction factors derived from PYTHIA 5 (black), PYTHIA 8 (red), and PYTHIA 8 Dire (teal).","label":"fig:phi_pt_1995","source":"arxiv","key":"a7747d025e4d84a83123e85dea2fe205","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/a7747d025e4d84a83123e85dea2fe205"},{"filename":"EEC_systs_1995.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Summary of the systematic uncertainties for 1995. The total uncertainty (gray dashed) is calculated as the quadratic sum of the individual uncertainty sources, including event and track selection corrections~\\ref{sec:selectionUncert} (orange), unfolding model dependence~\\ref{sec:unfoldingUncert} (red), matching scheme~\\ref{sec:matchingUncert} (blue), 2D binning projection~\\ref{sec:projectionUncert} (teal), unfolding regularization strength~\\ref{sec:unfoldingUncert} (brown), track efficiency (olive) and momentum scale (pink)~\\ref{sec:trkUncert}, and fake~\\ref{sec:trackTail} (gold).","label":"fig:phi_pt_1995","source":"arxiv","key":"c408cfbea08623114974073d4ee29aaf","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/c408cfbea08623114974073d4ee29aaf"},{"filename":"covariance_1995.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Covariance (left) and correlation (right) matrices of the one-dimensional EEC distribution as a function of $\\theta_{\\rm L}$ from 1995 data.","label":"fig:correlation_1995","source":"arxiv","key":"35c553bf34d3dbe1221847c7d20ad45f","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/35c553bf34d3dbe1221847c7d20ad45f"},{"filename":"correlation_1995.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Covariance (left) and correlation (right) matrices of the one-dimensional EEC distribution as a function of $\\theta_{\\rm L}$ from 1995 data.","label":"fig:correlation_1995","source":"arxiv","key":"df83f488d1d6cd90cb5beebd7698c70e","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/df83f488d1d6cd90cb5beebd7698c70e"},{"filename":"covariance_unfolded_1995.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Covariance (left) and correlation (right) matrices of the one-dimensional EEC distribution as a function of $\\theta_{\\rm L}$ after unfolding for 1995.","label":"fig:covUnfold_1995","source":"arxiv","key":"385a56213610bf18609c7a857d8784d4","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/385a56213610bf18609c7a857d8784d4"},{"filename":"correlation_unfolded_1995.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Covariance (left) and correlation (right) matrices of the one-dimensional EEC distribution as a function of $\\theta_{\\rm L}$ after unfolding for 1995.","label":"fig:covUnfold_1995","source":"arxiv","key":"06a3ad61d8364198e5d20db2983d0cf3","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/06a3ad61d8364198e5d20db2983d0cf3"},{"filename":"covariance_z_1995.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Covariance (left) and correlation (right) matrices of the one-dimensional EEC distribution as a function of $z$ from 1995 data.","label":"fig:correlation_z_1995","source":"arxiv","key":"64439a438897a74812b1c9b22f60ba80","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/64439a438897a74812b1c9b22f60ba80"},{"filename":"correlation_z_1995.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Covariance (left) and correlation (right) matrices of the one-dimensional EEC distribution as a function of $z$ from 1995 data.","label":"fig:correlation_z_1995","source":"arxiv","key":"c8b5ee0346e468e6d85a767b15e1009a","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/c8b5ee0346e468e6d85a767b15e1009a"},{"filename":"covariance_unfolded_z_1995.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Covariance (left) and correlation (right) matrices of the one-dimensional EEC distribution as a function of $z$ after unfolding for 1995.","label":"fig:covUnfold_z_1995","source":"arxiv","key":"c24e3fd3f247dedeec14e0f47c9308b4","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/c24e3fd3f247dedeec14e0f47c9308b4"},{"filename":"correlation_unfolded_z_1995.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Covariance (left) and correlation (right) matrices of the one-dimensional EEC distribution as a function of $z$ after unfolding for 1995.","label":"fig:covUnfold_z_1995","source":"arxiv","key":"df52ba0a39267b939b8282691969f1a7","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/df52ba0a39267b939b8282691969f1a7"},{"filename":"Thrust_Delphi_unf_size_1995.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Size of the unfolding correction: raw (black) and unfolded (red) data distributions for $\\tau$ (left) and $\\log\\tau$ (right). Also shown are the generator-level distributions from PYTHIA 5 (teal).","label":"fig:unfoldThrust1995","source":"arxiv","key":"f9fa02c4021aaba23e1b180f91d9b6da","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/f9fa02c4021aaba23e1b180f91d9b6da"},{"filename":"Thrust_log_unf_size_1995.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Size of the unfolding correction: raw (black) and unfolded (red) data distributions for $\\tau$ (left) and $\\log\\tau$ (right). Also shown are the generator-level distributions from PYTHIA 5 (teal).","label":"fig:unfoldThrust1995","source":"arxiv","key":"7b6229a9a497d84aff624382206f353a","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/7b6229a9a497d84aff624382206f353a"},{"filename":"Thrust_Delphi_sele_corr_comp_varEmin_1995.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Major systematic uncertainty: the relative uncertainty on the unfolded thrust distributions from varying the minimum neutral particle energy cut. The effect is shown as the ratio of the varied result (\\(E_{\\text{neutral}} > 5.0\\)~GeV) (red) to the nominal result (\\(E_{\\text{neutral}} > 0.5\\)~GeV) (black).","label":"fig:cutNeutral1995","source":"arxiv","key":"f2972e6cd0358a42d9ca393bdffa3a65","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/f2972e6cd0358a42d9ca393bdffa3a65"},{"filename":"Thrust_log_sele_corr_comp_varEmin_1995.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Major systematic uncertainty: the relative uncertainty on the unfolded thrust distributions from varying the minimum neutral particle energy cut. The effect is shown as the ratio of the varied result (\\(E_{\\text{neutral}} > 5.0\\)~GeV) (red) to the nominal result (\\(E_{\\text{neutral}} > 0.5\\)~GeV) (black).","label":"fig:cutNeutral1995","source":"arxiv","key":"8177a249a72ab0a5c27ace70d81c4cc5","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/8177a249a72ab0a5c27ace70d81c4cc5"},{"filename":"Thrust_Delphi_multiWeight_1995.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Major systematic uncertainty: effect of the event multiplicity reweighting on the reconstructed \\(\\tau\\) (left) and \\(\\log\\tau\\) (right) distributions. The nominal 1995 MC (red) is compared to the re-weighted 1995 MC (teal). The 1995 data is shown in black for reference.","label":"fig:multiCorr1995","source":"arxiv","key":"db6eafc7d40ddc77f0382be2a7161120","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/db6eafc7d40ddc77f0382be2a7161120"},{"filename":"Thrust_log_multiWeight_1995.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Major systematic uncertainty: effect of the event multiplicity reweighting on the reconstructed \\(\\tau\\) (left) and \\(\\log\\tau\\) (right) distributions. The nominal 1995 MC (red) is compared to the re-weighted 1995 MC (teal). The 1995 data is shown in black for reference.","label":"fig:multiCorr1995","source":"arxiv","key":"723fff14ba961f0a109911122f3ea616","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/723fff14ba961f0a109911122f3ea616"},{"filename":"Thrust_Delphi_unf_model_1995.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Major systematic uncertainty: unfolded thrust (left) and $\\log\\tau$ (right) distributions using response matrices derived from PYTHIA 5 (black), PYTHIA 8 (red), and PYTHIA 8 Dire (teal).","label":"fig:unfoldThrustModel1995","source":"arxiv","key":"1e4e676bc409d0a376a5d5444b563798","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/1e4e676bc409d0a376a5d5444b563798"},{"filename":"Thrust_log_unf_model_1995.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Major systematic uncertainty: unfolded thrust (left) and $\\log\\tau$ (right) distributions using response matrices derived from PYTHIA 5 (black), PYTHIA 8 (red), and PYTHIA 8 Dire (teal).","label":"fig:unfoldThrustModel1995","source":"arxiv","key":"7975ba7157f6acb3ae0aa6112bf53a7e","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/7975ba7157f6acb3ae0aa6112bf53a7e"},{"filename":"Thrust_Delphi_sele_corr_1995.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Major systematic uncertainty: unfolded $\\tau$ (left) and $\\log\\tau$ (right) distributions corrected by acceptance correction factors derived from PYTHIA 5 (black), PYTHIA 8 (red), and PYTHIA 8 Dire (teal).","label":"fig:corrThrustModel1995","source":"arxiv","key":"cfd2b37e7c79b31cd4229027ff18fafe","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/cfd2b37e7c79b31cd4229027ff18fafe"},{"filename":"Thrust_log_sele_corr_1995.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Major systematic uncertainty: unfolded $\\tau$ (left) and $\\log\\tau$ (right) distributions corrected by acceptance correction factors derived from PYTHIA 5 (black), PYTHIA 8 (red), and PYTHIA 8 Dire (teal).","label":"fig:corrThrustModel1995","source":"arxiv","key":"09be8c7e2a91fea63a39dd63011d01a8","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/09be8c7e2a91fea63a39dd63011d01a8"},{"filename":"Thrust_Delphi_systs_1995.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Summary of systematic uncertainties for $\\tau$ (left) and $\\log\\tau$ (right) measurements for 1995.","label":"fig:sysSummaryThrust1995","source":"arxiv","key":"d5c9bfe2b60700735fbc9c525030d757","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/d5c9bfe2b60700735fbc9c525030d757"},{"filename":"Thrust_log_systs_1995.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Summary of systematic uncertainties for $\\tau$ (left) and $\\log\\tau$ (right) measurements for 1995.","label":"fig:sysSummaryThrust1995","source":"arxiv","key":"9a9a6f249109fbcfc5bf3d2a8155e5af","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/9a9a6f249109fbcfc5bf3d2a8155e5af"},{"filename":"Thrust_C_Delphi_comp.png","material":"preprint","caption":"Comparison of the fully corrected track-only thrust from this analysis (using DELPHI open data) and the legacy DELPHI measurement~\\cite{DELPHI:2000uri}. Both results are based on 1994 data.","label":"fig:trackThrust","source":"arxiv","key":"07a2c4dc114d429fea89f51e93834ace","url":"https://inspirehep.net/files/07a2c4dc114d429fea89f51e93834ace"}],"collaborations":[{"value":"Electron-Positron Alliance"}],"inspire_categories":[{"term":"Experiment-HEP","source":"arxiv"},{"term":"Phenomenology-HEP","source":"arxiv"},{"term":"Experiment-Nucl","source":"arxiv"}],"preprint_date":"2025-10-21","accelerator_experiments":[{"legacy_name":"EPA","curated_relation":true,"record":{"$ref":"https://inspirehep.net/api/experiments/3083840"}}],"author_count":9,"first_author":{"emails":["jingyu.zhang@cern.ch"],"affiliations_identifiers":[{"schema":"ROR","value":"https://ror.org/02vm5rt34"}],"full_name":"Zhang, Jingyu","last_name":"Zhang","first_name":"Jingyu","recid":1290173},"control_number":3071639,"earliest_date":"2025-10-21","document_type":["article"],"texkeys":["Zhang:2025nlf"],"abstracts":[{"source":"arXiv","value":"Recent theoretical developments, as well as experimental measurements at hadron collisions, have renewed interest in studying event shape variables in $e^+e^-$ collisions. We present a measurement of thrust and track-based energy-energy correlator in $e^+e^-$ collisions at center-of-mass energy of 91.2 GeV, using newly released open data from the DELPHI experiment. The event shapes, measured with unprecedented resolution and precision, are compared to various Monte Carlo and analytic predictions. Leveraging DELPHI's unique detector geometry and reconstruction capabilities, the track energy-energy correlator measurement provides data with the highest angular resolution, offering critical inputs for precision tests of QCD in both collinear and back-to-back limits. This note presents the first physics analysis using DELPHI open data and establishes benchmarks necessary for future studies exploiting this legacy dataset.","abstract_source_suggest":{"input":"arXiv"}}],"primary_arxiv_category":["hep-ex"],"titles":[{"source":"arXiv","title":"Analysis note: measurement of thrust and track energy-energy correlator in $e^+e^-$ collisions at 91.2 GeV with DELPHI open data"},{"source":"arXiv","title":"Analysis note: measurement of thrust and track energy-energy correlator in e+e- collisions at 91.2 GeV with DELPHI open data"}],"facet_author_name":["1785106_Tzu-an Sheng","1756687_Hannah Bossi","1996199_Yu-Cheng Chen","1019977_Yen-Jie Lee","1069109_Yi Chen","1253756_Christopher Mcginn","1253749_Austin Alan Baty","1290173_Jingyu Zhang","1727473_Anthony Badea"],"core":true,"license":[{"license":"CC BY 4.0","material":"preprint","url":"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/"}],"_oai":{"sets":["Literature"],"id":"oai:inspirehep.net:3071639","updated":"2026-03-10T07:39:13.017438"},"curated":true,"arxiv_eprints":[{"categories":["hep-ex","hep-ph","nucl-ex"],"value":"2510.18762"}]},"id":"3071639","created":"2025-10-22T04:09:23.548200+00:00"}],"total":1},"links":{"self":"https://inspirehep.net/api/literature/?q=arxiv%3A2510.18762&size=1&page=1","bibtex":"https://inspirehep.net/api/literature/?q=arxiv%3A2510.18762&size=1&page=1&format=bibtex","latex-eu":"https://inspirehep.net/api/literature/?q=arxiv%3A2510.18762&size=1&page=1&format=latex-eu","latex-us":"https://inspirehep.net/api/literature/?q=arxiv%3A2510.18762&size=1&page=1&format=latex-us","json":"https://inspirehep.net/api/literature/?q=arxiv%3A2510.18762&size=1&page=1&format=json","json-expanded":"https://inspirehep.net/api/literature/?q=arxiv%3A2510.18762&size=1&page=1&format=json-expanded","cv":"https://inspirehep.net/api/literature/?q=arxiv%3A2510.18762&size=1&page=1&format=cv"}}